I"q<p>Use HTTPS instead of HTTP to connect. This is only required if you have enabled the setting “Enable HTTPS” in OpenWebif settings. <em>(e.g., on the remote by pressing <code>Menu</code>&gt;<code>Plugins</code>&gt;<code>OpenWebif</code>)</em>. You will need to ensure you have a valid CA certificate in place or SSL verification will fail with this component.</p>
